        <abstract> 
<p>Sends copy of <hi rend="italic">Nature</hi> in which EK’s letter, translated by Balfour, is printed. Thanks him. Now feels easy.</p>  
<p>G. J. Romanes’ language in his review of Butler’s book [<hi rend="italic">Unconscious memory</hi>] is perhaps too strong. Butler’s vanity is a "real psychological curiosity".</p> 
        </abstract>
